headline: Gold Within Whisker of $4,000 on US Shutdown, Tech Stock Wobble
summary: Investors are also monitoring signs the ebullience driven by artificial intelligence may have reached excessive levels, after a report on Oracle Corp.’s cloud margins, while a political crisis in France and a change of leadership in Japan are adding to the uncertainty.  Gold has soared more than 50% this year as President Donald Trump shook up trade and geopolitics, helping to spur a move away from the dollar.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. sees room for the rally to continue, raising its forecast for December 2026 to $4,900 an ounce, up from $4,300.
